[2]
Date: Sat 29 Jan 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Xinhuanet News Agency, Sat 29 Jan 2005 [edited]
<http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2005-01/29/content_2522925.htm>

Viet Nam; One more Death and Suspected Case ex Cambodia
---------------------------------------------------
On Friday [28 Jan 2005], a patient who lives in a Cambodian town adjacent
to Vietnam's southern Kien Giang province was admitted to the provincial
hospital of Kien Giang with avian influenza symptoms such as high
temperature and pneumonia.
Since 28 Dec 2004, a total of 16 people in Vietnam have been reported to
have contracted the H5N1 virus, of whom 10 (8 from the southern region and
2 from the northern region) have died. Altogether, 300 avian influenza
patients in the country have died since the disease [appeared] in December
2003. Since January 2005 [sic -- 2004?], bird flu has stricken 28 cities
and provinces in Viet Nam, including 6 in the northern region, killing and
leading to the forced culling of over 828 000 fowl, according to the
country's Department of Animal Health.
